SIMPLE: bucking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bucking
<hw>Buck"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of
soaking or boiling cloth in an alkaline liquid in the operation of
bleaching; also, the liquid used.</def> <rj><au>Tomlinson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A washing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The process of breaking up or pulverizing
ores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bucking iron</b></col> <fld>(Mining)</fld>, <cd>a
broad-faced hammer, used in bucking or breaking up ores.</cd> --
<col><b>Bucking kier</b></col> <fld>(Manuf.)</fld>, <cd>a large circular
boiler, or kier, used in bleaching.</cd> -- <col><b>Bucking
stool</b></col>, <cd>a washing block.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buckish</ent>⟦br⟧
